't collect as cash is fragile; >0.8\u00d7 means earnings are real cash, <0.6\u00d7 is an accrual red flag.","why_it_can_fail":"One-off working-capital swings or a capex year can distort a single ratio; the 5-yr median smooths it."},{"label":"Balance-sheet safety","value":0.53,"unit":"\u00d7 D/E","status":"ok","read":"Moderate leverage (D/E 0.53\u00d7, interest cover 3.3\u00d7).","meaning":"Latest debt-to-equity and interest coverage (EBIT \u00f7 interest) from the balance sheet.","why_useful":"Low debt and high interest cover let a business survive a downturn; high debt amplifies trouble.","why_it_can_fail":"Off-balance-sheet leases/guarantees aren't captured; a cash-rich firm can show low D/E yet still be risky elsewhere."},{"label":"Earnings momentum","value":52.73,"unit":"% YoY","status":"good","read":"Profit up 53% YoY (latest TTM) and accelerating.","meaning":"Trailing-twelve-month net profit vs the year-ago TTM (and whether the YoY rate is rising = 'accelerating').","why_useful":"Improving, accelerating earnings tend to drive re-rating; falling profit warns of a deteriorating business.","why_it_can_fail":"TTM can be lumpy for cyclicals/one-offs; cross-check the multi-year trend on the Fundamentals tab."}]},"valuation":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"pe_now":111.6,"pe_percentile":7.0,"median_pe":187.8,"earnings_yield_pct":0.9,"pb":9.21,"ev_ebitda":34.62,"quality_score":69.0,"pat_cagr_5y_pct":null,"peg":null,"cheapness":{"status":"good","read":"P/E at the 7-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 cheap vs its own history."},"expectations":"Trades at 111.6\u00d7 earnings; multi-year growth not estimable, so 'priced-in' growth is unclear.","cyclical_caveat":null,"meaning":"P/E percentile = where today's price-to-earnings sits within the stock's own last-10-yr range (low = cheap vs its past). Paired with the Quality score and 5-yr profit growth so a cheap multiple is judged against business strength, not in isolation.","why_useful":"Cheapness only matters relative to quality and growth \u2014 a low P/E on a declining or peak-cyclical business is a trap, not a bargain.","why_it_can_fail":"P/E breaks for loss-makers / one-offs; for banks use P/B not EV/EBITDA; a multiple cheap vs history can stay cheap if the business has structurally de-rated."},"ownership":{"ok":true,"na":null,"holders":{"Promoter":{"periods":["Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[32.45,32.43,32.43,32.39,32.35],"latest_pct":32.35,"chg_1y_pp":-0.1},"FII":{"periods":["Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[60.62,59.26,58.13,58.06,57.94],"latest_pct":57.94,"chg_1y_pp":-2.68},"DII":{"periods":["Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[5.21,6.44,7.92,7.78,7.83],"latest_pct":7.83,"chg_1y_pp":2.62},"Public":{"periods":["Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[1.74,1.87,1.52,1.78,1.87],"latest_pct":1.87,"chg_1y_pp":0.13}},"pledge":null,"events":[],"placeholders":[{"label":"Promoter pledge (detail)","note":"share-level pledge history \u2014 fetchable via NSE, deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Bulk / block deals","note":"large on-market trades \u2014 NSE feed, deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Insider / SAST disclosures","note":"promoter & designated-person dealings \u2014 deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Exchange announcements","note":"NSE/BSE filings stream \u2014 deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Results calendar","note":"next board-meeting / results date \u2014 deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Credit ratings","note":"rating-agency actions \u2014 deferred to MVP-2."}],"reads":{"Promoter":"Promoter stake down 0.10pp over ~1yr \u2192 32.35%.","FII":"FIIs reducing (-2.68pp YoY \u2192 57.94%).","DII":"DIIs adding (+2.62pp YoY \u2192 7.83%)."},"meaning":"Quarterly shareholding (% held by Promoters / Foreign (FII) / Domestic (DII) institutions / Public) from Screener, plus exchange corporate actions tagged by materiality (High = structural: bonus/split/buyback/merger; Low = routine: dividend/AGM).","why_useful":"Rising promoter & institutional ownership and clean corporate actions are confirming signals; falling promoter stake or pledging is a governance/skin-in-the-game warning.","why_it_can_fail":"Shareholding is a lagged quarterly snapshot; promoter % can fall for benign reasons (QIP, ESOP dilution). Pledge & insider detail are deferred (placeholders below)."},"snapshot":{"dimensions":{"Market":{"verdict":"neutral","score":0,"drivers":["\u2212 Below its 200-day average (-6%) \u2014 downtrend.","\u00b7 50-day average still below the 200-day (no golden cross).","+ Outpacing the NIFTY 500 by +18pp over 12 months."],"rule":"Points: +1 price above its 200-day average \u00b7 +1 a golden cross (50-day \u2265 200-day) \u00b7 +1 within 10% of the 52-week high \u00b7 +1 beating the NIFTY 500 over 12 months; \u22121 for each opposite, and \u22121 if more than 25% below its peak. Verdict: positive at +2 or more, negative at \u22122 or less, otherwise neutral."},"Business":{"verdict":"positive","score":2,"drivers":["\u00b7 Average quality (69/100).","+ 3.27\u00d7 of profit came in as operating cash (5-yr median) \u2014 well backed.","\u00b7 Moderate leverage (D/E 0.53\u00d7, interest cover 3.3\u00d7).","+ Profit up 53% YoY (latest TTM) and accelerating."],"rule":"Points across the four business flags: +1 for each that is 'good' (quality, cash conversion, balance-sheet safety, earnings momentum), \u22121 for each that is 'weak'. Verdict: positive at +2 or more, negative at \u22122 or less."},"Valuation":{"verdict":"positive","score":2,"drivers":["+ P/E at the 7-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 cheap vs its own history."],"rule":"Cheap \u2014 P/E below the 30th percentile of its own 10-year range \u2014 scores +2 (supportive); expensive (above the 70th) scores \u22122; mid-range is 0. A peak/cyclical-earnings flag discounts a cheap read to +1. NOTE: 'positive' means the multiple looks supportive vs the stock's OWN history \u2014 it is NOT a buy call."},"Owner